8. Technical Database Schema

To support the rule-based logic and financial tracking of the FleetFlow Digital Hub, a Relational Database Management System (RDBMS) like PostgreSQL or MySQL is recommended. This ensures data integrity—specifically, that fuel logs and trips cannot exist without being tied to a valid Vehicle ID.
8.1. Entity Relationship Diagram (ERD) Logic

The schema is designed around the Vehicle as the primary asset. All other tables (Trips, Maintenance, Fuel) use the vehicle_id as a Foreign Key to enable automated ROI and cost-per-km calculations.
8.2. Table Definitions
Table: Vehicles (Assets)
Column	Data Type	Constraints	Description
id	UUID	Primary Key	Unique internal identifier.
license_plate	String	Unique, Not Null	Physical plate number.
model	String	Not Null	e.g., "Ford Transit", "Volvo FH16".
max_capacity_kg	Float	Not Null	Used for load validation.
current_odometer	Float	Default: 0	Updated after every trip.
status	Enum	[Available, On Trip, In Shop, Retired]	Controls Dispatcher visibility.
Table: Drivers
Column	Data Type	Constraints	Description
id	UUID	Primary Key	Unique identifier.
full_name	String	Not Null	Driver's name.
license_expiry	Date	Not Null	Logic: If < current_date, block trip.
safety_score	Integer	Range 0-100	Calculated from completion rates.
status	Enum	[On Duty, Off Duty, Suspended]	Availability toggle.
Table: Trips
Column	Data Type	Constraints	Description
id	UUID	Primary Key	Unique trip ID.
vehicle_id	UUID	Foreign Key	References Vehicles.id.
driver_id	UUID	Foreign Key	References Drivers.id.
cargo_weight	Float	Not Null	Must be ≤ Vehicle Max Capacity.
status	Enum	[Draft, Dispatched, Completed, Cancelled]	Workflow state.
revenue	Decimal	Not Null	Gross income from the trip.
Table: Operational_Logs (Maintenance & Fuel)
Column	Data Type	Constraints	Description
id	UUID	Primary Key	Unique log ID.
vehicle_id	UUID	Foreign Key	Links cost to specific asset.
log_type	Enum	[Fuel, Maintenance]	Categorizes the expense.
amount_spent	Decimal	Not Null	Financial cost.
liters	Float	Nullable	Only populated if log_type is 'Fuel'.
entry_date	Timestamp	Not Null	Date of service or refueling.
8.3. Core Database Logic & Triggers

    Capacity Trigger: Before an INSERT into the Trips table, the system checks:
    CargoWeight≤(SELECT max_capacity_kg FROM Vehicles WHERE id=vehicle_id)

    Maintenance Hook: An INSERT into Operational_Logs with log_type = 'Maintenance' triggers an UPDATE on the Vehicles table, setting status = 'In Shop'.

    Odometer Update: Upon a Trip moving to Completed, the current_odometer in the Vehicles table is updated based on the distance logged in the trip details.

9. API Endpoint Specifications

To connect the frontend dashboard with the relational database, the system will use a RESTful API structure. All endpoints (except Login) require an Authorization: Bearer <token> header, with permissions enforced by the user's role.
9.1. Authentication & Users
Method	Endpoint	Description	Role Required
POST	/api/v1/auth/login	Returns JWT and User Role.	Public
GET	/api/v1/users/profile	Fetches current user details.	All
9.2. Asset & Driver Management
Method	Endpoint	Description	Role Required
GET	/api/v1/vehicles	List all vehicles (filterable by status/type).	All
POST	/api/v1/vehicles	Add a new vehicle to the registry.	Manager
PATCH	/api/v1/vehicles/:id	Update status (e.g., "Out of Service").	Manager
GET	/api/v1/drivers/available	List compliant drivers (not expired/suspended).	Dispatcher
9.3. Trip & Dispatch Operations
Method	Endpoint	Description	Role Required
POST	/api/v1/trips	Create a new trip. Triggers Capacity Check.	Dispatcher
GET	/api/v1/trips/:id	Fetch specific trip lifecycle details.	All
PUT	/api/v1/trips/:id/status	Update state: Dispatched → Completed.	Dispatcher
9.4. Maintenance & Financial Logs
Method	Endpoint	Description	Role Required
POST	/api/v1/logs/maintenance	Logs repair. Triggers Vehicle "In Shop" status.	Manager
POST	/api/v1/logs/fuel	Records fuel cost and liters for a vehicle.	Dispatcher/Manager
GET	/api/v1/analytics/roi	Returns calculated ROI and fuel efficiency data.	Financial Analyst
9.5. Example Request/Response Payload

